---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Modern Priesthood — Sun Worship — Nazaryah"
  description="Every religion has a priesthood. The language changed. The function did not. Three branches of the same tree — The Sacred Art, The Institutional Church, and NASA."
>
  <div class="sw-wrap">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="sw-hero">
      <p class="sw-label">&#8213; Sun Worship &#8213;</p>
      <h1 class="sw-title">The Modern Priesthood</h1>
      <p class="sw-sub">
        Every religion has a priesthood. The language changed. The function did not.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ── INTRO ── -->
    <section class="sw-section">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p>
          Every religion has a priesthood — a class of men who interpret reality for the masses, who speak with authority that is not to be questioned, and whose declarations are accepted on faith. The pagan world had the priests of Ra, the oracles of Delphi, the Magi of Persia. The medieval world had the Roman Catholic clergy. The modern world has three branches of the same tree — and they function identically to every priesthood that came before them.
        </p>
        <p>
          What changed was not the system. What changed was the language. The robes became lab coats. The temples became universities. The sacred texts became peer-reviewed journals. The incantations became equations. And the congregation — the billions of people who accept what they are told without ever independently verifying a single claim — remained exactly the same.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THREE BRANCHES ── -->
    <section class="sw-cta-section">
      <p class="sw-cta-label">&#8213; Three Branches &#8213;</p>
      <h2 class="sw-cta-title">One Tree, Three Expressions</h2>
      <p class="sw-cta-sub">
        The scientific establishment, the institutional church, and the space agency are not three separate systems.
      </p>

      <div class="sw-card-grid">

        <a href="/sun-worship/the-priesthood/the-sacred-art" class="sw-card">
          <span class="sw-card-title">Science</span>
          <span class="sw-card-poetic">The Sacred Art</span>
          <span class="sw-card-body">Before the 17th century, what we now call science was openly called the occult. Alchemy became chemistry. Astrology became astronomy. The names changed; the priesthood did not.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/sun-worship/the-priesthood/the-institutional-church" class="sw-card">
          <span class="sw-card-title">Church</span>
          <span class="sw-card-poetic">The Institutional Church</span>
          <span class="sw-card-body">False prophets, megachurch empires, and the New Apostolic Reformation — a network of self-appointed apostles seeking dominion over every sector of society.</span>
        </a>

        <a href="/sun-worship/the-priesthood/nasa" class="sw-card">
          <span class="sw-card-title">NASA</span>
          <span class="sw-card-poetic">The New Priesthood</span>
          <span class="sw-card-body">Built by an occultist, staffed by Nazis — a space agency that functions as a religious institution demanding faith in images no one can verify.</span>
        </a>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── THREE BRANCHES ONE TREE ── -->
    <section class="sw-section sw-section-alt">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <p class="sw-section-heading">Three Branches, One Tree</p>
        <p>
          The scientific branch provides the intellectual framework. It tells you how reality works — that the sun is at the center, that the earth is a spinning ball, that the universe is billions of years old, and that you are an insignificant accident in an incomprehensibly vast cosmos. It replaced the Hermetic Art with a new name, but the cosmological conclusions are identical to those of the ancient sun worshippers: the sun is supreme, and man is small.
        </p>
        <p>
          The institutional church provides the spiritual cover. It baptized the pagan calendar, the pagan symbols, and the pagan hierarchy into a system that calls itself Christian but operates according to the principles of Mithras, Sol Invictus, and Babylon. It tells you that the Torah was abolished, that the Sabbath was moved, and that the Creator's name doesn't matter — all of which keep you from reading Scripture with unclouded eyes.
        </p>
        <p>
          The space establishment provides the visual proof. It gives you the images, the models, the narratives that make the sun-centered cosmology feel real. Without NASA's composites, without the Hubble photographs, without the CGI animations of spinning globes — the entire heliocentric model collapses back into what it always was: a philosophical claim, not an observed fact.
        </p>
        <p>
          Together, these three branches accomplish what no single institution could do alone: they construct an entire reality — intellectual, spiritual, and visual — that places the sun at the center and moves Yahuah's earth, Yahuah's creation, and Yahuah's people to the margins.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── SCRIPTURE ── -->
    <section class="sw-section">
      <div class="sw-prose">
        <div class="sw-scripture-block">
          <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; 2 Corinthians 11:14&#8211;15</p>
          <p>"And no marvel; for Satan himself is transformed into an angel of light. Therefore it is no great thing if his ministers also be transformed as the ministers of righteousness; whose end shall be according to their works."</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sw-scripture-block" style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">
          <p class="sw-scripture-label">&#9656; Colossians 2:8</p>
          <p>"Beware lest any man spoil you through philosophy and vain deceit, after the tradition of men, after the rudiments of the world, and not after the Messiah."</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── QUOTE ── -->
    <section class="sw-footer-quote">
      <p class="sw-quote-text">"Transformed. Not absent — transformed. The ministers of darkness do not announce themselves. They wear the clothing of light."</p>
      <p class="sw-quote-ref">— 2 Corinthians 11:14</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .sw-wrap {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0e0904 0%, #1a1208 20%, #160f07 100%);
    color: #f0e0bf;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    min-height: 80vh;
  }

  .sw-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #4a3218;
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 0%, rgba(180, 100, 20, 0.2), transparent 70%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0602 0%, #1a1208 100%);
  }

  .sw-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    color: #8a6028;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sw-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .sw-sub {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    color: #c4a46b;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .sw-section {
    padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2e1f0d;
  }

  .sw-section-alt {
    background: rgba(10, 6, 2, 0.3);
  }

  .sw-prose {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: #d9c9a8;
  }

  .sw-prose p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .sw-prose p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .sw-section-heading {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem !important;
  }

  .sw-scripture-block {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-left: 3px solid #BA7517;
    background: rgba(10, 6, 2, 0.4);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }

  .sw-scripture-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #BA7517;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem !important;
  }

  /* ── CTA SECTION ── */
  .sw-cta-section {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2e1f0d;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 50%, rgba(100, 60, 20, 0.12), transparent 70%);
  }

  .sw-cta-label {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    color: #6a4820;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .sw-cta-title {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #f0e0bf;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  .sw-cta-sub {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #c4ad84;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 560px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ── Card grid (3-part button format) ── */
  .sw-card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 1040px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .sw-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    text-align: left;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 1.75rem 1.5rem 1.6rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #7a3a14 0%, #5e2a0c 55%, #3d1a08 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(186, 117, 23, 0.35);
    border-radius: 14px;
    box-shadow:
      0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.55),
      inset 0 2px 4px rgba(220, 160, 80, 0.25),
      inset 0 -2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .sw-card:hover {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #965a3e 0%, #7a3a14 55%, #5e2a0c 100%);
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow:
      0 10px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.65),
      inset 0 2px 4px rgba(220, 170, 100, 0.3),
      inset 0 -2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
  }

  .sw-card-title {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #fff5e0;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .sw-card-poetic {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: #f0d8a4;
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .sw-card-body {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Crimson Pro', 'Crimson Text', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #f5e8c8;
  }

  .sw-footer-quote {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #160f07 0%, #0e0904 100%);
  }

  .sw-quote-text {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.2rem);
    font-style: italic;
    color: #c4a46b;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .sw-quote-ref {
    font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: #5a3e1a;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .sw-card-grid { gap: 1.25rem; }
    .sw-card { padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem; }
    .sw-card-title { font-size: 1.3rem; letter-spacing: 2.5px; }
  }
</style>
